Every detail has been curated with both style and functionality in mind, from the smart design to the luxury finishes. Located just steps from Grapevines vibrant shops, restaurants, and entertainment, Dove Station offers the perfect blend of peaceful neighborhood living and dynamic city access. Live in luxury. Every home has a story. This one just happens to have chapters that span more than a century. Welcome to the GE Hurst Historical Houseoriginally constructed in 1910 and reborn in 2018 through a meticulous renovation that preserved its soul while anchoring it in the now. Set on a lush .54-acre lot filled with mature native trees, this home feels like a page out of Grapevines past with a future-proof foundationliterallybuilt atop a modern steel pier-and-beam system. With over 4, 560 square feet under roof and 2, 780 square feet of conditioned living space, the layout is as thoughtful as it is functional. Downstairs, the primary suite offers privacy and comfort with a spa-like en suite bath, while a guest suite on the same floor provides hospitality with ease. A light-filled great room flows into the heart of the homean updated kitchen and dining area designed for gathering. Upstairs, two additional bedrooms each feature full baths, accompanied by a large second living area and an expansive office space that could double as a creative studio or library. The details tell the real storypreserved trimwork, wide-plank floors, antique-inspired fixturesall balanced by smart updates and energy-efficient systems. Outside, a 960 sq ft detached garage-workshop echoes the aesthetic of a classic Texas barn, offering functionality with curb appeal. And the porte-cochere near the mudroom and laundry isnt just a design featureits a daily convenience. This is more than a historical homeits a legacy, lovingly restored and ready for its next chapter.

text: Wait to you see this immaculate single story home. As you enter this lovely home, in the living room, you will find a stone fireplace, wet bar, built-ins, can lights and picture trim moldings. The dining room has a pretty glass block wall. You can look out to the backyard and pool area from the family room and breakfast room through the wall of windows. The family room has natural light from the skylight. The kitchen is large with lots of cabinets (lazy susan, pantry and deep size cabinets for pots), stainless appliances (gas cooktop range with double ovens), granite counters, stone backsplash, breakfast bar and a skylight for natural light. Primary bedroom is large and has access to the backyard-pool area. Primary bathroom has a jet tub, frameless shower, granite counter vanity with two sinks, and walk in closet with Elfa shelving. The two secondary bedrooms are a good size and have a Jack and Jill bathroom (granite counter vanity with two sinks). The third living area is truly a flex space (can use for study, work out area, playroom, etc). Take a dip and refresh in your pool. It is salt water and has LED colored lighting. Nice size yard with plush landscaping, long driveway to the rear entry garage. There is shelving in the garage. Many updates: wood floors, flooring, windows, water heater, HVAC, lights, fixtures, fans, paint, cabinets, granite counters, appliances, Elfa shelving.

The home offers two spacious bedrooms, two full baths, and large closets. In addition to the main living spaces, there's a dedicated office and a separate storage roomthe office has previously been used as a small third bedroom, providing flexible use of space. Outside, you'll find a two-car garage, a two-car carport, and a small studio or workshop, perfect for art, hobbies, or extra storage. A truly unique property with versatile spaces to fit your lifestyle.

text: OPEN HOUSE Sat 1-3 and Sun 1-3. Welcome to this exquisite estate just a quarter mile from Lake Grapevine and minutes from the charm of Historic Downtown Grapevine. Thoughtfully redesigned for modern living and effortless entertaining, this 4 bedroom, 3.5 bathroom home with 3 car garage offers unmatched comfort inside and out. Inside a seamless blend of modern finishes and classic touches create an inviting ambiance, perfect for both everyday living and unforgettable entertaining. The expansive rooms have curated details at every turn. The primary suite is a true sanctuary, complete with a spa inspired bath and custom closets offering elegant organization. The open living spaces are enhanced by an abundance of windows in every room and complimented by a seamless Sonos sound system inside and out, including 10 mounted TVs installed by Starpower, with multiple zones designed for entertaining and immersive entertainment. The backyard shines with outdoor spaces that are nothing short of resort-inspired. A newly installed custom pool and spa with tanning ledge and table seating create a private oasis, enhanced by a fully equipped summer kitchen and multiple lounge areas ideal for al fresco dining. Adding to the estate's exceptional versatility is a charming climate controlled she shed and the detached climate-controlled building with full electric, perfect for, a private office, gym or workshop. A standout whole-home Generac generator installed in 2023 offers peace of mind year-round, along with updated electric and plumbing. Updated sprinkler system and landscaping, with a picturesque front courtyard with turf, provide an enchanting welcome and striking curb appeal. Set in one of North Texas most desirable locations, with quick access to DFW Airport, scenic walking trails, and vibrant local attractions, this estate offers a lifestyle of luxury, comfort, and everyday indulgence. This is more than a home, it's a destination.

Discover this meticulously maintained single story pool home nestled on a corner lot located just minutes to Grapevine Lake and Dove Park. Don't miss this great duplex in the desired neighborhood of Courtney Square. Both sides are for sale. This beautifully updated duplex offers the perfect blend of comfort and style. Featuring two spacious bedrooms and two full baths, this home also includes a versatile sunroom ideal for use as a home office, reading nook, or hobby space. This home features luxury vinyl plank throughout the living areas and bedrooms, complemented by durable tile in the kitchen and baths. Freshly painted both inside and out, the home feels bright and inviting from the moment you arrive. The kitchen boasts granite countertops, a convenient breakfast bar, and newly painted cabinets. The living room has a cozy fireplace and adjacent is the dining room featuring a door that goes out to the private patio, perfect for outdoor dining or simply relaxing with your morning coffee. Updates include replaced roof, gutters, foundation reinforcement as well as replaced HVAC in 2019. This duplex is move-in ready and waiting to become your new home. Close to Main Street, Great Wolf Lodge, and the Gaylord. Schedule your showing today.

Luxury, comfort, and impeccable design meet in this stunning custom home, ideally located near major highways and perched on one of Tarrant Countys highest elevations. This thoughtfully upgraded residence features 10 ceilings (9 upstairs), 8 doors, maple cabinetry, and premium surfaces including travertine, marble, granite, and onyx. The chefs kitchen boasts granite counters, pot filler, warming oven, dual fridge hookups, and a massive 10 x 10 walk-in pantry. Entertain in style at the onyx-lit wet bar or relax in the spacious living area with one of three fireplaces. The primary suite offers electronic shades, custom Closet by Design system, and a spa-like bath with oversized whirlpool tub, walk-in shower with dual heads, rain head, and body sprays. Major upgrades include PEX plumbing, foam insulation, Lutron lighting, whole-house water filtration with reverse osmosis (stubbed to all bathrooms), hot water recirculation, intercom system, and a full alarm with 4 keypads. A workshop with HVAC, water heater, and laundry adds incredible versatility. Additional features: electric gate, locking mailbox, touchpad entries, grade 4 imitation slate roof ($100K+), pool bath, cedar panic room, and never lived in by pets. Just a short walk to WT Parr Park and located in a 500-year flood zone. This home combines elegance, efficiency, and convenience in one extraordinary package. Dont miss your chance to own it. text: Nestled in a peaceful cul-de-sac just minutes from Lake Grapevine, scenic trails, parks, and the festive charm of downtown Grapevineknown as the Christmas Capital of Texas! Separate utility room supports oversized appliances. Attic is full encapsulation on underside of roof with radiant barrier for reduced utility costs. Relax on the private back patio while enjoying the conveniences of the surrounding Grapevine amenities! Two car garage detached with epoxy flooring, artificial back yard grass, driveway gate and outdoor back patio. See list of upgrades, utilities fees and all other documents loaded in transaction file.

text: Nestled in the heart of the Grapevine Historic District, this stunning Victorian-style home seamlessly blends timeless 19th-century charm with the modern conveniences of a home built in 2004. text: Location, location, plus this updated 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath home in this sought after Colleyville Grapevine school district is ready for you. Entering the home, you find yourself in the spacious foyer accented with a cascading staircase leading up to the secondary bedrooms and a bons loft. The foyer shares a view of the formal living and formal dining. The home has recently updated with has a 50 yr. roof with transferable warranty. Even more recent updates include interior paint, fresh updated carpet, and some tile work. You will enjoy the large, centralized kitchen with a breakfast bar, granite counters and tile backsplash. This centralized kitchen allows you to be a part of the home's daily activities. The rear family room with its gas log fireplace and built in cabinets and bookshelves invites a warm setting for entertaining. There is a half bath located off the kitchen and family room area. The kitchen has immediate access to the formal dining room located off the formal living area. The owner's retreat is located on the main level separated away from the central activity area of the home. With its updated luxury bath, the ensuite bath offers dual vanities, a separate tub and a glass walk in shower. The large walk-in closet gives you room for all seasons of clothing. Upstairs you will find a loft area just made for a home office, reading area or TV watching. There are three nice size bedrooms and a bath too. The rear entry driveway and garage offer some extra parking. An entry from the rear yard brings you into storage, mud room with access into the home. The home includes 2 water heaters and 3 Zoned HVAC units.

text: Sought after location! Walking distance to historic Main street, festivals, dining and Trinity Metro Tex Rail. Easy access to Hwy 114 and DFW Airport. Well maintained craftsman style home on large lot with mature trees. Split floor plan with spacious master bedroom and walk in closet. Generous kitchen cabinets and counter space. Flex room can be used as second dining or office. New HVAC and exterior doors in 2024. Move in Ready!

Come see this spacious, updated and completely move in ready home with a fabulous floorplan. Great natural light thoughout with a large living room featuring a painted wood burning fireplace and wood look flooring. Updated kitchen with a gorgeous Corian countertop, remodeled with updated cabinets 2022, stainless steel appliances and hardware. The windows throughout have been replaced with gorgeous vinyl windows in 2016. Fresh paint, updated lighting, updated switches, plugs, and GFCI's throughout. The primary bedroom is spacious and has two walk in closets, a built in desk with shelves and a spacious ensuite bathroom with a remodeled shower with seat, separate vanities, and garden tub. The gameroom can be used for a second living, a private office, or a media room. The bedrooms are all spacious and have walk in closets. The floorplan is split for added privacy. The garage hall bedroom has a builtin desk with shelves as well. The location is convenient with easy access to highways, shopping, dining, and entertainment. Don't miss this amazing Grapevine Gem.

New construction!!! Welcome to The Grapevine Brownstones Phase 2! This a a limited opportunity to own a luxury Lock and Leave Residence in the heart of Grapevine across from Hotel Vin, steps from Historic Main St, Peace Plaza, Harvest Hall and The Grapevine REC. A short walk across Dallas Rd to the TEX Rail which will drop you at DFW Airport or Ft. Worth and the The Grapevine Vintage RR with special excursions including the Stockyards and the Christmas Train. Only one Vintner Residence is left unsold, the highly sought after home is situated on a corner with a beautiful Bay and side windows. This Residence is 4 stories with 3 bdrm, 3.5 bath, 2 car garage and a 4th floor rooftop patio. Features include 12 foot ceilings in the kitchen and living room with a beautiful bay window and a third floor balcony. The homes are built elevator ready and buyers have option to install after closing. Enjoy a front row seat to many of the special events Grapevine offers including Main St Days, Grapefest, and all that comes with being The Christmas Capital of Texas. Walking is easy with a 75 Walkscore and also quick access to highways, Southlake Town Square, and DFW Airport. Residences pictured are representative of Phase 2 homes which are not yet under construction and estimated to be completed 2nd quarter of 2026.

Beautifully updated 4 bedroom, 2.5 bath located just one block from Grapevine Elementary School in highly rated Grapevine ISD! This home has been cherished for decades by the same family and is now ready for its new family. Downstairs has all hard flooring including the stairs. Upstairs has brand new carpet, paint, bathtub and ceiling fans. The home has one living room downstairs with another living or flex space upstairs in addition to 4 bedrooms. A separate office, dining room and owner suite are all located downstairs. The kitchen is bright and spacious and opens to the living room. The backyard is tranquil and provides a serene space to enjoy your mornings, evenings and weekends. The lot has many tall, mature trees. Buyer and buyer's agent to verify schools and square footage.

text: Back to Market. Buyers financing fell out. Seller is Open to Owner Financing, see terms in transaction desk. Welcome to this move-in ready condo offering the perfect blend of convenience and low-maintenance living. Located in the vibrant heart of Grapevine, this two-story home features an inviting layout. The oversized primary bedroom upstairs boasts a private balcony, ensuite bath, and a spacious walk-in closet. Two additional bedrooms on the second floor share a full bath, making it ideal for families or guests. Enjoy the ease of a dedicated full-sized laundry room, with a half bath conveniently located on the first floor. Step outside to your private courtyard, perfect for relaxing or entertaining, with direct access to a two-car garage that includes a large secure outdoor storage closet. This home is within walking distance of a nearby elementary school and scenic lake trails, ideal for outdoor enthusiasts. With HOA covering exterior maintenance and yard care, youll enjoy more free time to take advantage of the community clubhouse and pool. Conveniently located close to Grapevines best shopping, dining, Grapevine Lake, and DFW Airport, this condo truly has it all!

Welcome to the Millican House, a one-of-a-kind luxury home in the Historic District, walking distance from Main Street. Originally built in 1935 as a Sears kit house, this property has been carefully preserved and rebuilt into an approximately 3, 935 square foot masterpiece. The current homeowners have thoughtfully preserved portions of the original house, adding to the charm and character of this stunning home. This property boasts four bedrooms and four bathrooms, providing ample space for comfortable living. The primary bedroom, study and an open floor plan built for entertaining are all conveniently located on the first floor. The guest house features a living area, bathroom and bedroom, perfect for hosting guests or as a private retreat. Venture outside and enjoy the refreshing cocktail pool, outdoor kitchen and living center, surrounded by plenty of lawn space for play. With its prime location in the Historic District, this property offers a unique opportunity to own a piece of history while enjoying modern amenities and comforts. We invite you to come and see this stunning property for yourself. Welcome home!

text: Nestled on just under half an acre, mere minutes from Lake Grapevine, vineyards, campgrounds, marina, & elementary school, this incredible property is the one you've been searching for. Situated perfectly on a pie-shaped cul-de-sac lot, this charming cottage-style home boasts 3 bedrooms, 2.5 baths, spacious family room with WB fireplace, eat-in kitchen with breakfast bar, abundant cabinet & counter space, breakfast nook. Private oversized primary suite features an en-suite bath. Upstairs, an open loft provides the perfect space to entertain, complemented by 2 additional bedrooms & full bath. Backyard oasis is the ideal setting for family & entertaining, featuring a built-in Gunite Bromine pool with new equipment, sail shade cover, large grassy areas on both sides, & built-in basketball goal off the extended driveway & security gate. Updates include new roof in August 2024, fresh exterior paint, new HVAC system in 2022, 6-zone sprinkler system. This all-electric home is move-in ready.
